- format = '%m/%d'

%h1= "Iteration #{iteration}"
%a(href="http://www.agilesherpa.org/agile_coach/index.php") (A handy reference to agile project management.)

%h2 About

%p
  Pantheon is a game framework that does something radically simple: it describes game worlds in game terms rather than code terms.
  It has a special emphasis on expressive language, and testability. Pantheon runs on Mono, and therefore can be used by any CLR
  language, including C#, but the most powerful features require Boo -- a CLR dialect of Python (used by Unity) with powerful macro
  system that allows the language to be taught new things.

